# Feature Label And Changelog Rule

- Before implementation starts, ask the developer to provide a plain-language feature label.
- When summarizing completed work, always state the agent feature label as well.
- If the developer label and agent label differ, keep both labels in the changelog entry.
- Before any commit, append one new entry under `## [Unreleased]` in `CHANGELOG.md`.
- Each changelog entry must include:
  - `Developer label`
  - `Agent label`
  - `Changes` list with at least one concrete bullet
- Keep change bullets specific and reviewable (what changed and where).
- Prefer commit subjects that align with the developer feature label.
